In the class com.atlassian.confluence.pages.BlogPostsCalendar, the method getPostsForMonth inefficiently calls a method in the for loop.

        for(int i = 1; i <= getDaysInMonth(); i++)
        {
            for(BlogPost bp:getPostsForDay(i))
            {
                monthPosts.add(bp);
            }
        }

Here, for each for-loop iteration, the value of i is compared to the value returned by the getDaysInMonth() method, which for the i iterations of that for-loop shouldn't change. This is a performance hit and can be changed to something like : 

        int daysInMonths = getDaysInMonth();

        for(int i = 1; i <= daysInMonths ; i++)
        {
            for(BlogPost bp:getPostsForDay(i))
            {
                monthPosts.add(bp);
            }
        }

